This paper discusses the optimization of deep neural networks in the context of generative adversarial networks (GANs) and actor-critic methods in reinforcement learning (RL). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CV (Computer Vision) since GANs are commonly used in image generation tasks. The paper also discusses strategies for stabilizing training, which is relevant to optimization techniques in neural networks, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) a likely category. Finally, the paper discusses the connection between GANs and actor-critic methods, which are commonly used in control systems, making cs.SY (Systems and Control) a possible category as well.
